# Flutter Install on Ubuntu 20  LTS


## Android Studio Set Up

Yes, you MUST have Android Studio to run flutter!

### Install Java 

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-11-jdk
java --version 
```

Your output should be:

	openjdk 11.0.14 2022-01-18
	OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 11.0.14+9-Ubuntu-0ubuntu2.20.04)
	OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 11.0.14+9-Ubuntu-0ubuntu2.20.04, mixed mode, sharing)


### Install Android Studio
Try using snap first to install - it's easier...
```bash
sudo snap install android-studio --classic
```
Add private key to apt android studio repository and Install android-studio package:

Click ENTER to add repository key
```bash
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:maarten-fonville/android-studio
sudo apt install android-studio
```

### Android Studio Set up

[Click here for android studio set up tutorial with screenshots ](https://linuxhint.com/install_android_studio_ubuntu/)

## Flutter 

### Install 
```bash
sudo snap install flutter --classic
flutter doctor
```


### VSCode 

You need to have git installed first 

```bash
sudo apt install git
```

Install flutter extension 
For more information : https://docs.flutter.dev/development/tools/vs-code 

Flutter docs: 

https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/editor 

Flutter on vscode - extension etc...
https://docs.flutter.dev/development/tools/vs-code

https://docs.flutter.dev/development/tools/vs-code

